text: I'm starting to see some queries at work that remind me of <@U286Q175Y>’s "this will take days to finish" queries for edhrec
Super small town I’m passing through has a functional  drive up A&W
I had one in my home town growing up.
Well, they’ve got one thing going for them at least
The car hops are on skates
Remember when Sonic used to do that?
My son is flabbergasted by the whole thing
Probably no more so than by your use of the word flabbergasted.
haha, girls on skates is always a nice draw for fast food
Sonics around here still have that on occasion
I always think of Terry/Nick Swardson from Reno 911 when I think of carhops on skates.
I think that's the right way of thinking
I was unpacking and found that I have every season on DVD so I started rewatching. I forgot how spoiled Netflix makes you in that regard
When I had to swap the disc I instantly scoffed with "Netflix would NEVER do this to me"
DVDs never ask you if you’re still watching in that judgey way
That’s true.
Yes, I’ve been sitting here for 3 hours
I had a long day
Fuck you netflix, what I do with my entire weekend is my own business you asshole!
Speaking of wasting a weekend, our director just told everyone we could leave a couple hours early
YAY PAID LEAVE!
This whole "having holidays off" is weird. How do all you folks do it?
… I had a half day today and will not be back til Monday XD
Who's your boss again DM?
The Government
Like, your bosses boss
The Government :stuck_out_tongue:
WHo's the head of said government?
You know, technically, the people should be the boss of the government :stuck_out_tongue:
But who is the head of the executive branch of the current government?
Don't YOU know? :stuck_out_tongue:
But I'm asking you as my inside man
Verifying my information
When did I EVER agree to be your anything man :stuck_out_tongue:
ZOMG WHY ARE YOU AVOIDING MY QUESTIONS!?!?!
Because no one wants to admit they work for Annoying Orange.
This guy gets it
That was what I was getting at
I just wanted to call DM a "Trump supporter" since he technically works "for" him
But I don't want to be kicked out of restaurants :stuck_out_tongue:
Then say what you mean, <@U33EGB4TX>   Not all of us have all day of paid time off like some to wander around the point.
Oh I'm still on the clock right now
But realy, I'm jealous of weeklong vacations <@U6YMA7NAV>
I did have to take a day of leave, but I'm like a week away from having use-or-lose again
That's fair
Yesterday was my first day of 6 weeks off
It’s...it’s pretty nice
Education pay may suck, but the schedule is admittedly nice
6 weeks off? Fuck.
Yep. Would have been 10, but decided to do summer school, cause dollars
Flip some collections in your time off.
That requires capital haha
I started with just $45
Just tried to buy a collection actually. Dude wanted $60 for 1000 bulk and some rares
I was thinking about selling off some of the bulk in my collection for additional capitol.
So collection in the loosest sense of the word haha
Did he post as selling, or did you post as looking?
I actually just perused the area BST groups and there were quite a few collections out there. I'm meeting with a couple with my spare time later.
As selling. He wouldn’t budge.
This being the Bible Belt, there don’t seem to be as many old collections as other places. Devil cards and what have you
In Springfield we had an areawide MTG group that kept people pretty connected and collection sales like Dana's been scoring scarce. There isn't anything like that here...
Try posting saying you're looking. I was surprised.
Also, this is happening to my friend as we speak:
I might do that
Ha
Apparently people collect crayons
There’s a group for everyone
Oh shit, they found a torch red? That's like a Black Lotus in the Crayola community
Wait, you actually know about this shit?
Do you not?
I'm not a crayon aficionado.
It was found in the communal bin at Barnes and Noble.
I actually don't know anything about crayons but I'm not surprised
Check eBay
I looked. Didn't see one listed.
Jason Alt on his next collection hunt "Yeah, I'll take the cards, and if you'll throw in all your Crayola Crayons I'll toss in an extra $15."
Can we talk about the Crayola Reserve List?
Let's, please.

Maize, lemon yellow, blue gray, raw umber, green blue, orange red, orange yellow, and violet blue are the original Prismatic 8 retired colors and it sucks because I deserve to be able to doodle with them. Crayola management are idiots for maintaining a retired colors list that prevents me from using these awesome hues. I could find them but they're insanely expensive and I have every right to paint my stick figures in original colors.

And before you ask, no, I never actually plan on entering into Vintage crayon tournaments, but that doesn't mean i don't deserve access to these colors. The Retired Colors list is killing creativity...
Do you just want it for your casual multi person doodles?
I don't just want it...I deserve it!
Good for you
Does that make the Flesh colored crayon the Invoke Prejudice in this situation?
so racy...
